# SECTION 3 — PRODUCTION PIPELINE SPECIFICATIONS {#section-3}

## 3.1 Asset Generation Pipeline (Multi-GPU Agent Workflow)

```
STAGE 1 — SCRIPT
  Input  : This markdown file
  Task   : Extract avatar dialogue from AUDIO_SCRIPT blocks per episode
  Output : Plain text dialogue files per episode

STAGE 2 — AUDIO (TTS Agent)
  Tool   : ElevenLabs / Coqui TTS / OpenVoice
  Voice  : Professional Male News Anchor
  Speed  : 1.1x
  Tone   : Authoritative, calm, urgent on key terms
  Output : WAV/MP3 per episode segment (intro, act1, act2, act3, outro)

STAGE 3 — MUSIC (AI Music Agent)
  Tool   : MusicGen / Suno AI / Udio
  Prompt : "Cinematic tension, financial news, minor key, 140 BPM, no lyrics, orchestral electronic hybrid"
  Stems  : Melody + bass + percussion (separate stems for mixing)
  Output : WAV stems per episode + brand sting (2 sec)

STAGE 4 — IMAGES (Image Generation Agent)
  Tool   : Stable Diffusion XL / Flux / Midjourney
  Prompts: See IMAGE_SCRIPT block per episode
  Seed   : Use consistent seed for avatar across all 10 episodes
  Output : PNG 1920x1080 per scene + PNG 1280x720 thumbnail base

STAGE 5 — VIDEO (Video Generation Agent)
  Tool   : RunwayML Gen-3 / Kling / Pika / HeyGen (avatar)
  Avatar : D-ID or HeyGen — consistent presenter, business casual
  B-Roll : Pexels API + AI generation for custom shots
  Output : MP4 per shot at 4K 24fps

STAGE 6 — CHARTS (Data Viz Agent)
  Tool   : Python (matplotlib / plotly / manim)
  Style  : Dark background #0A1628, gold #D4AF37, teal #1A6B6B accent lines
  Output : MP4 animation 1920x1080 at 15fps, transparent-bg PNG stills

STAGE 7 — THUMBNAIL (Composite Agent)
  Tool   : SDXL base image + Photoshop / Canva API / Pillow
  Spec   : 1280x720 px, safe zone 1180x620 px center
  Output : 2 variants (A/B test) per episode as PNG

STAGE 8 — STITCH (FFmpeg Pipeline Agent)
  Input  : Audio (stage 2) + Music (stage 3) + Video/Avatar (stage 5) + Charts (stage 6)
  Tool   : FFmpeg
  Timeline: Per SCREENPLAY block timestamps per episode
  Export  : 4K H.264 MP4 for YouTube | 1080p H.265 for Reels (9:16 crop)

STAGE 9 — UPLOAD (Distribution Agent)
  YouTube : Title + Description + Tags from episode spec
  Reels   : 9:16 crop + caption from REELS_SCRIPT block
  Schedule: Tuesday–Thursday 2–4 PM EST
```

