### STORY
We open in 1971 — Nixon closes the gold window. Cut to 2025 — the dollar falls 11% in one half-year, its worst performance since the 1973 oil crisis. We follow the money: central banks dumping US Treasuries, BRICS nations building payment alternatives, Trump openly welcoming a weaker dollar. We examine what a reserve currency actually is, why it matters to ordinary people, and what history tells us about what happens when reserve currencies shift. We end with the investor's dilemma: where does wealth hide when the world's reserve currency wobbles?

